# This is the configuration file for your powerline-shell prompt
# Every time you make a change to this file, run install.py to apply changes
#
# For instructions on how to use the powerline-shell.py script, see the README

# Add, remove or rearrange these segments to customize what you see on the shell
# prompt. Any segment you add must be present in the segments/ directory

# virtual_env - Show current virtual environment (see http://www.virtualenv.org/)
# username - Show the current user's username as in ordinary prompts
# hostname - Show the machine's hostname. Mostly used when ssh-ing into other machines
# ssh - Show a padlock when ssh-ing from another machine
# cwd - Show the current directory. If the path is too long, the middle part is replaced with ellipsis ('...')
# read_only - Show a padlock if the current user has no write access to the current directory
# git - Show the current git branch and status
# hg - Show the current mercurial branch and status
# svn - Show the current svn branch and status
# fossil - Show the current fossil branch and status
# jobs - Show number of running jobs
# root - Shows a '#' if the current user is root, '$' otherwise, also, changes color if the last command exited with a non-zero error code
SEGMENTS = virtual_env username hostname ssh cwd read_only git hg svn fossil jobs root


# Change the colors used to draw individual segments in your prompt
THEME = default
